<item>
            <title>[LU-4509] clio can be stuck in osc_extent_wait</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4509</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Assume scenario like this:&lt;br/&gt;
 1) thread-1 held an active extent&lt;br/&gt;
 2) thread-2 called flush cache, and marked this extent as &quot;urgent&quot; and &quot;sync_wait&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
 3) thread-3 wants to write to the same extent, osc_extent_find will get &quot;conflict&quot; because this extent is &quot;sync_wait&quot;, so it starts to wait...&lt;br/&gt;
 4) cl_writeback_work has been scheduled by thread-4 to write some other extents, it has sent RPCs but not returned yet.&lt;br/&gt;
 5) thread-1 finished his work, and called osc_extent_release()&lt;del&gt;&amp;gt; osc_io_unplug_async()&lt;/del&gt;&amp;gt;ptlrpcd_queue_work(), but found cl_writeback_work is still running, so it&apos;s ignored (-EBUSY)&lt;br/&gt;
 6) thread-3 is stuck because nobody will wake him up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is an issue I hit while testing DAOS, but it should be addressed in common code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
